caption: A gorgeous little spot in the area. We used to pick up at least once a week and were never disappointed. Charlie used to work at Paneantico, so he has experience in the business. Love the sandwiches. Always a friendly, great experience. My personal favorite is their Chicken Parmesan sandwich. They have super fast service as well, considering how many busy they get. It's a very worthwhile place to try.
Excellent sandwich. We'll worth the wait!

I feel the sandwiches are tasty but I don't like the bread for a $12 hero.  I think you should have rolls as well.  Pricey for this type of food. I feel the quality of the bread 🍞 has be better for Italian sandwiches.  Bay Ridge you can get away prices
Bread is on point. $12 for a chicken parm which is reasonable. Can get a little pricey with certain items, but worth it. Very tasty.

Did some searching and saw this place had good reviews. Trying to feed 19 people we called ahead and ordered for pick up. Place had the sandwiches done in the exact time they said they would and they were deserving of EVERY. SINGLE. STAR. Literally everyone was talking about how good their sandwich was. I can’t decide if the food or the service was better. Super great guys behind the counter. We live in park slope but I’ll be back. It’s worth the travel. Do yourself a favor and grab some grub from this place. You will not regret it.
Hidden gem in the neighborhood! Noone around had fresh pastrami, but they did, homemade & delicious! Friendly service too. Will definitely return & recommend them.

Forget about being the best sandwich shop in Bay Ridge, this place has to be the best sandwich shop in New York City. Doesn't matter what you order, it's going to be good. The roast beef that Charlie makes is out of this world. Your going to pay $10 to $12 for a hero here, but worth every penny.

I was there the day this place opened. Best fresh Mozzarella in Brooklyn,  when ever I am headed to a big family meal I always stop into to pick up a fresh ball of Mozzarella to take with me. This isn't fast food, so be patient.  This family run gem is what Brooklyn is about. Experience the real Brooklyn, No hipsters here.   If you are  hungry one of Charlie's sandwich's will fill you to capacity. Plan for a nap or a double shot of espresso when you are done. If your not hungry considering splitting a sandwich with some one.  My favorite is the Shrimp Parm or a Hero with Soprasatta and Mozzarella.
